{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599779","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599779"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:59:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:59:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15597"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15597","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15597"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8288"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70386"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8288"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15597"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55850"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5103"},{"type":"tags","id":"10126"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20010"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20011"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70386","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70386"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA histological section of thyroid tissue shows tall columnar follicular cells with increased vascularity. The colloid within the follicles appears irregular at the edges.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological features best confirms the diagnosis of Graves\u0027 disease?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Non-caseating granulomas","Dense stromal fibrosis","Scalloped colloid margins","Lymphocytic infiltration","Oncocytic cell changes"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn Graves\u0027 disease, the thyroid gland shows several characteristic histological features. The most distinctive finding is \u003Cstrong\u003Escalloped colloid margins\u003C/strong\u003E within follicles, indicating active hormone production and release. The follicular cells are typically tall, columnar and hyperplastic with increased vascularity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-caseating granulomas\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of subacute (de Quervain\u0027s) thyroiditis\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDense stromal fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is seen in Riedel\u0027s thyroiditis\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDense \u003Cstrong\u003Elymphocytic infiltration\u003C/strong\u003E is typical of Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOncocytic cell changes\u003C/strong\u003E (formerly called Hurthle cells) can be seen in both Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis and other thyroid conditions but are not characteristic of Graves\u0027 disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe scalloped appearance occurs due to increased endocytosis of thyroid colloid by stimulated follicular cells, creating an irregular border at the colloid-cell interface.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Graves\u0027 disease histology shows hyperplastic follicular cells, scalloped colloid, and increased vascularity","Scalloping of colloid indicates increased thyroid hormone production and release","Thyroid follicles normally contain homogeneous colloid with smooth edges"],"references":["Lane LC, Wood CL, Cheetham T. Graves\u0027 disease: moving forwards. Arch Dis Child. 2023 Apr;108(4):276-281. doi: 10.1136/archdischild-2022-323905. Epub 2022 Jul 13. PMID: 35831126; PMCID: PMC10086272","Girgis CM, Champion BL, Wall JR. Current concepts in graves\u0027 disease. Ther Adv Endocrinol Metab. 2011 Jun;2(3):135-44. doi: 10.1177/2042018811408488. PMID: 23148179; PMCID: PMC3474632","De Leo S, Lee SY, Braverman LE. Hyperthyroidism. Lancet. 2016 Aug 27;388(10047):906-918. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(16)00278-6. Epub 2016 Mar 30. PMID: 27038492; PMCID: PMC5014602","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55850"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15597"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55850","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55850"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-14T20:16:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-14T20:29:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8288"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70386"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"ty